{"id": 223697572, "title": "UK tourists warned to avoid baggage error or face being 'splattering", "text": "A baggage handler has shared an absolute no-no for people taking holidays when it comes to packing. Zack, who works for a company providing ground baggage services, has revealed a list of packing errors people often make when travelling. Among them is how people pack toiletries. He said a major no-no was to put liquids on the outside of a suitcase - unless you want them to be \"squished.\" Speaking to Conde Nast, he warned against placing liquids like shampoo in outside pockets as other baggage could be stacked on top, causing them to splatter. He added: \"The baggage holds are not glamorous. Luggage is squished and stacked, and bags packed full survive this better.\" Read more: Tourists warned of rare Canary Island weather phenomenon Furthermore, Zack highlighted the importance of securely zipping up your bag, revealing that it's common to receive luggage with open pockets. He said: \"I cannot tell you how many times luggage comes to me with open pockets, dumping out everything the moment I pick it up.\" Elsewhere, just because your luggage is pricey, that doesn't guarantee it'll be handled with extra care, Zack cautioned. He said: \"I see a lot of Louis Vuitton luggage, but having an expensive bag doesn't mean I'm going to treat it with kid gloves.\" \"Don't complain if your bag gets dirt on it; a bag is designed to protect the contents, not itself.\"", "summary": "An airport baggage handler has revealed the &quot;number one thing&quot; all passengers need to ensure their bags are safe from damage - and it isn't what you might expect", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/travel/uk-tourists-warned-avoid-baggage-29242501", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/incoming/article24472030.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/1_Baggage-handlers-unload-bags-at-Birmingham-Airport.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:29:39", "author": "Jordan Coussins", "